# Fixture FM7: Trailing semicolon after last predicate-object pair is valid.
#
# Hypothesis: An implementation that requires a verb + objectList after every
# semicolon will reject this valid syntax, producing a parse error.
#
# Expected: parse succeeds; exactly one triple:
#   <http://example/s> <http://example/p> <http://example/o> .
#
# Divergence signal: AcceptRejectSplit — strict-grammar implementation
# rejects; conformant one accepts the bare trailing semicolon.
#
# Spec: Turtle §2.5.1 grammar:
#   predicateObjectList ::= verb objectList (';' (verb objectList)?)*
# The `?` makes the (verb objectList) after ';' optional.
# Errata: w3c/rdf-tests issue #152.

<http://example/s> <http://example/p> <http://example/o> ; .
<http://example/s2> <http://example/p> <http://example/o1> ;
                    <http://example/q> <http://example/o2> ; .
